title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter should display in data set dialog
description: When executing a stored procedure from Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, on the query result page, no data is returned. The expected behavior is that the output parameter should display in the edit data set dialog.
OB: On the query result page, no data is returned.
EB: The output parameter should display in the edit data set dialog.
SR: 1. Call the stored procedure from Oracle database. 2. Navigate to the query result page. 3. Observe that no data is displayed. 4. Expected behavior: The output parameter should be visible in the edit data set dialog.
